  <discussion>Ptychostomum pallescens is a common widespread boreal-temperate species favoring wet soil in wetlands, along streams, and in springs. The costal awns are pigmented. Ptychostomum creberrimum is similar, but has smaller spores, synoicous sexual condition, and ovate segment perforations.</discussion>
